properties.Summary:
Description: Snow squalls expected tonight into Sunday. Snow squalls are expected to develop tonight as cold northwesterly winds develop over Lake Huron. properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Rain, at times heavy, is expected. A Pacific frontal system will bring rain to West and North Vancouver Island. 50 to 70 mm of rain is forecast by Sunday evening for most communities of West Vancouver Island and North Vancouver Island including Tofino and Port Hardy. However higher rainfall amounts are forecast near Zeballos and near Port Alice where 100 mm of rain is anticipated by Sunday evening. ### Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.
